{"article_id":"AkY1pJsygl5Ibxez","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Just a day after declaring","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"her cabinet united behind her","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"in pursuing a new Brexit plan ,","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"UK prime minister Theresa May stands on the brink of political oblivion .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"Four of her cabinet ministers resigned today ,","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"including Brexit secretary Dominic Raab ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"setting up a very difficult vote in Parliament over the plan :","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"The morning after the night before was a rough one for British Prime Minister Theresa May .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"On Wednesday night , she announced","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"that she ' d won her cabinet ' s backing for her draft proposal","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"on how the U.K. should pull out of the European Union .","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"On Thursday morning , May ' s Brexit secretary , the man","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"who led her negotiating team in Brussels","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"to hammer out that draft ,","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"quit , along with another member of her cabinet and several junior ministers .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"Dominic Raab , the second of May ' s Brexit secretaries","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"to quit the role in as many years ,","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"the draft agreement","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"reached with Brussels","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"would effectively leave Britain beholden to the rules and regulations of the European Union","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"and even give the EU the power","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"to stop the U.K. from extricating itself down the road .","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"he could not \" in good conscious support the terms \" of the deal","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"he helped to craft .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"Raab wasn ' t the only member of May ' s government","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"to walk out on Thursday .","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"Her Junior Northern Ireland minister Shailesh Vara , junior Brexit minister Suella Braverman , and parliamentary private secretary Anne-Marie Trevelyan also stepped down .","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"Prospects for approval for May ' s draft agreement look slim","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"- and chances","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"it will come to a vote at all","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"are less than solid , too .","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"May could well face a vote of no confidence","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"before Parliament even gets a chance","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"to consider the draft agreement :","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"BREAKING","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"Eurosceptic Tory leader Jacob Rees-Mogg to submit letter of no confidence in Theresa May as Conservative leader later today ,","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"sources confirm","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"- Christopher Hope","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"( @ christopherhope )","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"November 15 , 2018","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"That may be a little premature ,","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"according to Sky News reporter Kate McCann :","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"I understand","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"Brady DID NOT confirm number of letters with the chief whip ,","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"so that sounds like a meeting","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"to prepare the ground .","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"Source with knowledge of the meeting said","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"they don ' t believe","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"he ' s hit the magic 48 ... yet .","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"- Kate McCann","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"( @ KateEMcCann )","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"November 15 , 2018","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"Still , Rees-Mogg pointed out what he clearly sees as May ' s failings in the agreement","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"and asks ,","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"\" Should I not write to my right honourable friend , the member for Altringham , and sail west ? \"","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"This has some parallels to the Nancy Pelosi leadership fight in the US .","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"There seem to be a number of Tories unhappy with May ,","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"but not too many people ready to challenge for leadership , even among the hardline Brexiters .","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"Raab insisted","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"that he wants May to remain in place :","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"I think","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"she needs a Brexit secretary","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"that will pursue the deal","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"that she wants to put to the country with conviction .","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"I don ' t feel","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"I can do that in good conscience .","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"But I respect her ,","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"I hold her in high esteem ,","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"I think","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"she should continue ,","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"but I do think","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"we need to change course on Brexit .","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"The issues","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"created by the draft agreement","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"go well beyond resigning ministers .","depth":5},{"id":77,"text":"After having reviewed the draft agreement ,","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"Scotland ' s first minister declared","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"that it would result in a new and successful Scottish independence vote :","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"It was \" reasonable \" to think","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"that the timing of a possible new vote on secession would depend on how Britain ' s current political chaos over Brexit played out ,","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"she told Scotland ' s devolved parliament .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"\" That time will come ,","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"and","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"when it does","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"I have no doubt","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"that the people of Scotland will choose to be independent , \"","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"she said .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"Sturgeon and others in the Scots parliament were angered by terms in the agreement","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"they claim","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"benefit Northern Ireland at their expense .","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"\" This is not an academic or abstract argument , \"","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"Sturgeon declared ,","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"\" but has real consequences for jobs and living standards in Scotland. \"","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"She also called for David Mundell to resign from May ' s cabinet ,","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"as he had promised to do in a letter to the leader of the Scottish Conservative Party weeks earlier","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"if a deal emerged","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"that \" threatened the integrity of the UK ' s internal market . \"","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"May gamely tried selling the plan to a skeptical Commons ,","depth":5},{"id":101,"text":"but ended up admitting","depth":6},{"id":102,"text":"that the deal could lock the entire UK into the backstop EU customs-union arrangement for the foreseeable future .","depth":6},{"id":103,"text":"The problem ,","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"May said ,","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"is that this is the best deal","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"that could be arranged","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"- and the only deal","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"that gets the UK back its territorial sovereignty :","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"Theresa May has admitted","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"she \" shares concerns \"","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"that the UK could be locked into the backstop arrangement , amid testy exchanges in the House of Commons","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"following the departure of two cabinet ministers .","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"... Iain Duncan Smith , the former Tory leader , said","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"he had serious misgivings about the backstop ,","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"the UK maintained the \" sovereign right","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"to leave bodies like Nato and the UN \"","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"but would not have that right over the backstop arrangement .","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"In her reply to Smith , May accepted","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"that coming out of the backstop would require mutual consent .","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"\" I won ' t make any bones about that , \"","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"she said .","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"\" Across the house there are concerns in relations to the backstop","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"and I share some of their concerns ,","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"these have not been easy decisions","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"to take .","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"It has been necessary","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"and would be necessary in any deal","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"we were striking . \"","depth":13},{"id":130,"text":"It looks like the Tories won ' t be satisfied with just control over immigration .","depth":2},{"id":131,"text":"If May presses ahead with this deal ,","depth":3},{"id":132,"text":"the Tories might turn to new leadership with more hardline Brexit views ,","depth":4},{"id":133,"text":"which will likely produce a crash-out of the EU and a hard border in Ireland .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":267,"left":263,"right":266,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":263,"left":207,"right":262,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":207,"left":140,"right":206,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":137,"right":139,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":136,"right":3,"relation